00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.499
JP SOUCHAK: Whether you're just
starting out on your journey

00:00:02.499 --> 00:00:04.135
toward a career in
Android development,

00:00:04.135 --> 00:00:05.760
or you have been
working has an Android

00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:08.640
developer for some time,
you might ask yourself,

00:00:08.640 --> 00:00:12.210
how can I separate myself from
the pack and get recognized?

00:00:12.210 --> 00:00:14.910
Introducing the Associate
Android Developer certification

00:00:14.910 --> 00:00:17.460
by Google, an achievement
available to those

00:00:17.460 --> 00:00:21.610
who can display the skills of an
entry level Android developer.

00:00:21.610 --> 00:00:23.020
The first step on
your journey is

00:00:23.020 --> 00:00:25.630
determining if you're
ready to take the exam.

00:00:25.630 --> 00:00:28.480
Start by learning
what the exam covers.

00:00:28.480 --> 00:00:30.550
Review the skills that
you'll need to demonstrate

00:00:30.550 --> 00:00:32.280
when taking the exam.

00:00:32.280 --> 00:00:34.300
Next, decide whether
you need training

00:00:34.300 --> 00:00:36.420
or are ready to take the exam.

00:00:36.420 --> 00:00:39.450
Training is available
online, as well as in person.

00:00:39.450 --> 00:00:43.320
Also, training is available in
some colleges and universities.

00:00:43.320 --> 00:00:46.110
When you're ready, sign
up and take the exam.

00:00:46.110 --> 00:00:49.320
As part of the sign up,
you'll pay an exam fee.

00:00:49.320 --> 00:00:52.890
If you live in India,
you'll pay 6,500 rupee.

00:00:52.890 --> 00:00:57.690
If you live outside of
India, you'll pay $149.

00:00:57.690 --> 00:01:00.460
After you've signed
up and paid the fee,

00:01:00.460 --> 00:01:04.019
you will download the exam and
load it into Android Studio

00:01:04.019 --> 00:01:05.170
and begin.

00:01:05.170 --> 00:01:08.320
The exam's a timed,
performance-based assessment

00:01:08.320 --> 00:01:10.860
in which you'll implement
new features and debug

00:01:10.860 --> 00:01:13.470
issues in an existing app.

00:01:13.470 --> 00:01:17.340
When you start the exam,
you'll have 24 hours to finish.

00:01:17.340 --> 00:01:21.120
And once you're done, you'll
submit the exam for grading.

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:23.460
Your submission will be
evaluated through a combination

00:01:23.460 --> 00:01:26.010
of machine and human grading.

00:01:26.010 --> 00:01:28.050
Based on the outcome
of machine grading,

00:01:28.050 --> 00:01:30.780
you'll move on to
the exit interview.

00:01:30.780 --> 00:01:33.690
After you've finished, and
you've passed your interview,

00:01:33.690 --> 00:01:35.790
you will then receive
a mark from Google

00:01:35.790 --> 00:01:39.420
and join our community of Google
Certified Associate Android

00:01:39.420 --> 00:01:41.070
developers.

00:01:41.070 --> 00:01:44.470
Once you are certified, you can
share your mark on your resume,

00:01:44.470 --> 00:01:48.600
LinkedIn, G+, Twitter, and
in your email signature.

